CommandTestUtil and TypicalPersons used 2 different groups of people for different tests in the test suite, making it hard to keep track of the details of the people used and can cause some regressions when changes are made.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change use cases and fix numbering
commitResults.messageBody:
Split use cases to handle a single entity. For example, one use case for editing a staff and one for a guest.

Also fixed the numbering for extensions in use cases. Extensions should be the same number as the situation that occurs prior to it happening.
For example if a and b occur in MSS (numbered 1 and 2). Instead of b occuring, c can occurs (c is the extension). c should be numbered 1 instead of 2

Used getGuest and getVendor instead of getFilteredGuestList and getFilteredVendorList as deleting a person who is not currently shown on the list would throw an error when the filter command is implemented.
